#encoding UTF-8
<div class="entry-content blog-outer" itemprop="text">
    <br>
    <h2>Welcome to your new blog page!</h2>
    <p>Thank you for installing the <a href="https://github.com/poblabs/weewx-belchertown" target="_blank">Belchertown weewx skin</a>!</p>
    <p>This is your default blog page. To change this text:
    <ul>
        <li>Create a new file at <code>skins/Belchertown/blog.inc</code>, or rename the <code>skins/Belchertown/blog.inc.example</code> file to <code>blog.inc</code></li>
        <li>Use the example text within <code>skins/Belchertown/blog.inc.example</code> to create your blog page description!</li>
        <li>Full HTML, and weewx variables are accepted.</li>
    </ul>
    </p>
    <p>To show built in weewx variables (like station battery status (if supported), temperature, weewx version, etc.), just add them to this file. For example:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Station hardware: $station.hardware</li>
        <li>Server uptime: $station.os_uptime.long_form</li>
        <li>WeeWX uptime: $station.uptime.long_form</li>
        <li>WeeWX version: $station.version</li>
        <li>Belchertown Skin Version: $belchertown_version</li>
    </ul>
    <p>For an example of what this page could say, please see <a href="https://belchertownweather.com/blog" target="_blank">https://belchertownweather.com/blog</a>. If you need more help, refer to <a href="https://github.com/poblabs/weewx-belchertown#creating-blog-page-and-records-page" target="_blank">this link.</a></p>
    <p>Enjoy your new weewx skin!</p>
</div>
